comment:
Basically the ai model is learning from data. Gpt was trained primarily in autoregressive and supervised manner. It’s architecture is based on transformers which is nothing new. Models based on that architecture usually learn to predict next word in a sequence. Now, when you analyze data that you are training it on, you can deduce what is „expected” to be predicted.

Imagine that in training data everything starting with a given prefix relates to a given subject. Now using that prefix when the model is trained could result in setting a model in such a state that would result in answers related to that subject.

So basically when you train a model on a given data, you can analyze this data to have an idea what to expect. You could even format that data to your liking.

Btw. you can think of gpt as a probabilistic space modeled to fit a data as best as it can. That probabilistic space, based on input, calculates what is the most likely word to come up next in a sequence in a given context.

Btw2. If you are wondering if openai created some new technology, they did not. They just trained what’s known but on a big ass data using a big ass variantion of a known model architecture.
